ire, England":"Jórvík, England","Nottinghamshire, England":"Nottinghamshire, England, United Kingdom","England":"England"},"nl":{"Abt 1105–1178":"circa 1105–1178","1090–1132":"1090–1132","1130–1161":"1130–1161","1105–1178":"1105–1178","Abt 1130":"circa 1130","1106":"1106","1090":"1090","1105":"1105","Aft 1132":"na 1132","1178":"1178","before 1130":"vóór 1130","Aft 1161":"na 1161","1132":"1132","Abt 1105":"circa 1105","1130":"1130","1161":"1161","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Nottinghamshire, England":"Nottinghamshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","England":"England"},"en":{"Abt 1105–1178":"about 1105–1178","1090–1132":"1090–1132","1130–1161":"1130–1161","1105–1178":"1105–1178","Abt 1130":"about 1130","1106":"1106","1090":"1090","1105":"1105","Aft 1132":"after 1132","1178":"1178","before 1130":"before 1130","Aft 1161":"after 1161","1132":"1132","Abt 1105":"about 1105","1130":"1130","1161":"1161","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Nottinghamshire, England":"Nottinghamshire, England, United Kingdom","England":"England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Lovetot","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English:","from Anglo-Norman French <i>louet</i> ‘wolf-cub’, a diminutive of <i>lou</i> ‘wolf’. The nickname may also have been used as a personal name. Compare   Love  ,   Lovell  ,   Low  .","from the Middle English female personal name <i>Luvot</i> or <i>Lovet</i>, pet forms of   Love  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Lovette","meanings":["English: altered form of   Lovett  ."]},{"name":"Lovitt","meanings":["Scottish and English: variant of   Lovett  ."]},{"name":"Love","meanings":["English: from a Middle English personal name derived from the Old English female name <i>Lufu</i> ‘love’, or the masculine equivalent <i>Lufa</i>. Compare   Leaf   2.","English and Scottish: nickname from Anglo-Norman French <i>love</i> ‘she-wolf’ or simply ‘wolf’, the word <i>love</i> being a back-formation from the diminutive forms <i>lovel</i> and <i>lovet</i> ‘little wolf’. See also   Low   3, from Anglo-Norman French <i>lou</i>, the more usual form of the word.","Scottish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Fhionghuin</b> (see   McKinnon  )."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705185,"age":1,"year":"1106","julianDay":2125018,"title":"The Battle of Tichebray","description":"King Henry I defeated and captured his brother, Robert of Normandy, at the Battle of Tinchebray in 1106. Robert remained in captivity until his death in 1134.","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"William de Lovetot Lord of Hallamshire was born about 1105. He married Emma before 1130, in England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1178, in Yorkshire, England, at the age of 74."},"et":{"Abt 1105–1178":"umbes 1105–1178","1090–1132":"1090–1132","1130–1161":"1130–1161","1105–1178":"1105–1178","Abt 1130":"umbes 1130","1106":"1106","1090":"1090","1105":"1105","Aft 1132":"pärast 1132","1178":"1178","before 1130":"enne 1130","Aft 1161":"pärast 1161","1132":"1132","Abt 1105":"umbes 1105","1130":"1130","1161":"1161","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Nottinghamshire, England":"Nottinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"England"},"fi":{"Abt 1105–1178":"noin 1105–1178","1090–1132":"1090–1132","1130–1161":"1130–1161","1105–1178":"1105–1178","Abt 1130":"noin 1130","1106":"1106","1090":"1090","1105":"1105","Aft 1132":"1132 jälkeen","1178":"1178","before 1130":"ennen vuotta 1130","Aft 1161":"1161 jälkeen","1132":"1132","Abt 1105":"noin 1105","1130":"1130","1161":"1161","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Nottinghamshire, England":"Nottinghamshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"England"},"fr":{"Abt 1105–1178":"environ 1105–1178","1090–1132":"1090–1132","1130–1161":"1130–1161","1105–1178":"1105–1178","Abt 1130":"environ 1130","1106":"1106","1090":"1090","1105":"1105","Aft 1132":"après 1132","1178":"1178","before 1130":"avant 1130","Aft 1161":"après 1161","1132":"1132","Abt 1105":"environ 1105","1130":"1130","1161":"1161","Yorkshire, England":"Everwyck, Angleterre","Nottinghamshire, England":"Nottinghamshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","England":"Angleterre","lifeSummary":"William de Lovetot Lord of Hallamshire est né environ 1105. Il a épousé Emma avant 1130, à Angleterre. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils. Il est décédé en 1178, à Everwyck, Angleterre, à l’âge de 74 ans."},"de":{"Abt 1105–1178":"um 1105–1178","1090–1132":"1090–1132","1130–1161":"1130–1161","1105–1178":"1105–1178","Abt 1130":"um 1130","11